{"ts": "2026-06-07T23:27:02.877788+00:00", "update": {"tools": {"messages": [{"type": "tool", "data": {"content": [{"type": "text", "text": "successfully downloaded text file (SHA: 8f0fb941d50dbdb6233ecf221771bdf5425016bf)", "id": "lc_5205373b-e3a1-4b60-b917-b4e6fc8f2bbb"}, {"type": "text", "text": "import { createRouter, createWebHashHistory } from 'vue-router'\nimport Home from '../views/Home.vue'\n\nconst history = createWebHashHistory()\nconst routes = [\n  {\n    path: '/',\n    name: 'Home',\n    component: Home,\n    meta: {\n      layout: 'default',\n    },\n  },\n  {\n    path: '/about',\n    name: 'About',\n    // route level code-splitting\n    // this generates a separate chunk (about.[hash].js) for this route\n    // which is lazy-loaded when the route is visited.\n    component: () => import(/* webpackChunkName: \"about\" */ '../views/About.vue'),\n    meta: {\n      layout: 'default',\n    },\n  },\n]\nconst router = createRouter({\n  linkActiveClass: 'active',\n  history,\n  routes,\n})\n\nexport { router }\n", "id": "lc_b660a796-cfe6-4527-bcc2-266be10736ce"}], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "type": "tool", "name": "get_file_contents", "id": "30e1c8c2-6abe-4941-ba38-055efb3b86ad", "tool_call_id": "call_00_pgSincmNXokcqczvdSF37309", "artifact": null, "status": "success"}}]}}}
{"ts": "2026-06-07T23:27:10.731735+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "Here are the setup and day-to-day development commands for this project, which is a **Vue.js 3 Vite starter template** (using **pnpm** as the package manager).\n\n---\n\n## Verification: Inspected Files\n\n### `package.json` (full contents)\n\n```json\n{\n  \"name\": \"vue3-vite-starter-template\",\n  \"description\": \"Vue.js 3 Vite starter template with Pinia, Vue Router, Bootstrap and more.\",\n  \"version\": \"0.0.0-semantic-release\",\n  \"license\": \"MIT\",\n  \"repository\": \"https://github.com/kouts/vue3-vite-starter-template\",\n  \"packageManager\": \"pnpm@10.20.0\",\n  \"type\": \"module\",\n  \"scripts\": {\n    \"preinstall\": \"npx only-allow pnpm\",\n    \"dev\": \"vite\",\n    \"build\": \"vite build\",\n    \"preview\": \"vite preview\",\n    \"build-preview\": \"vite build && vite preview\",\n    \"lint\": \"eslint \\\"**/*.{vue,ts,js}\\\"\",\n    \"lint-fix\": \"eslint --fix \\\"**/*.{vue,ts,js}\\\"\",\n    \"test:unit\": \"vitest\",\n    \"test:unit-coverage\": \"vitest run --coverage\",\n    \"prepare\": \"husky\"\n  },\n  \"dependencies\": {\n    \"bootstrap\": \"^5.3.8\",\n    \"jsdom\": \"^27.1.0\",\n    \"pinia\": \"^3.0.3\",\n    \"vitest\": \"^4.0.6\",\n    \"vue\": \"^3.5.22\",\n    \"vue-router\": \"^4.6.3\"\n  },\n  \"devDependencies\": {\n    \"@commitlint/cli\": \"^20.1.0\",\n    \"@commitlint/config-conventional\": \"^20.0.0\",\n    \"@fullhuman/postcss-purgecss\": \"^7.0.2\",\n    \"@fullhuman/vue-cli-plugin-purgecss\": \"^7.0.2\",\n    \"@kouts/eslint-config\": \"^3.0.9\",\n    \"@vitejs/plugin-vue\": \"^6.0.1\",\n    \"@vue/compiler-sfc\": \"^3.5.22\",\n    \"@vue/test-utils\": \"^2.4.6\",\n    \"autoprefixer\": \"^10.4.21\",\n    \"eslint\": \"^9.39.0\",\n    \"husky\": \"^9.1.7\",\n    \"lint-staged\": \"^16.2.6\",\n    \"prettier\": \"^3.6.2\",\n    \"sass\": \"^1.93.3\",\n    \"vite\": \"^7.1.12\",\n    \"vite-plugin-html\": \"^3.2.2\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\n### `src/router/index.js` (full contents)\n\n```js\nimport { createRouter, createWebHashHistory } from 'vue-router'\nimport Home from '../views/Home.vue'\n\nconst history = createWebHashHistory()\nconst routes = [\n  {\n    path: '/',\n    name: 'Home',\n    component: Home,\n    meta: {\n      layout: 'default',\n    },\n  },\n  {\n    path: '/about',\n    name: 'About',\n    // route level code-splitting\n    // this generates a separate chunk (about.[hash].js) for this route\n    // which is lazy-loaded when the route is visited.\n    component: () => import(/* webpackChunkName: \"about\" */ '../views/About.vue'),\n    meta: {\n      layout: 'default',\n    },\n  },\n]\nconst router = createRouter({\n  linkActiveClass: 'active',\n  history,\n  routes,\n})\n\nexport { router }\n```\n\n---\n\n## Setup & Day-to-Day Development Commands\n\n| Action | Command |\n|---|---|\n| **Install dependencies** | `pnpm install` |\n| **Start dev server (hot-reload)** | `pnpm run dev` |\n| **Build for production** | `pnpm run build` |\n| **Preview production build** | `pnpm run preview` |\n| **Build + preview** | `pnpm run build-preview` |\n| **Run unit tests** (vitest, watch mode) | `pnpm run test:unit` |\n| **Run unit tests with coverage** | `pnpm run test:unit-coverage` |\n| **Lint all source files** | `pnpm run lint` |\n| **Lint and auto-fix** | `pnpm run lint-fix` |\n\n**Note:** The project enforces **pnpm** as the only allowed package manager (via a `preinstall` script that runs `npx only-allow pnpm`), so always use `pnpm` rather than `npm` or `yarn`.", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 1240, "prompt_tokens": 8000, "total_tokens": 9240, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": null, "reasoning_tokens": 193, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": null, "cached_tokens": 7680}, "prompt_cache_hit_t